ğŸ­ What is Abstraction?
ğŸ“˜ Definition:
Abstraction ka matlab hai:
Sirf essential cheezein show karo, baaki details chhupa lo.

Matlab:

User ko kya kaam karna hai, woh dikhate ho

Kaise ho raha hai, woh chhupa lete ho (implementation hidden)

ğŸ§â€â™‚ï¸ Real Life Example:
Soch â€” Car chalate waqt:

Tumhe pata hota hai: steering ghumao, brake dabao

But andar engine kaise kaam karta hai, woh abstract hai!

ğŸ¯ Goal of Abstraction:
User ko simple interface do

Complex logic hide karo

System ko secure aur clean rakho

ğŸ› ï¸ Java mein Abstraction kaise hoti hai?
Java provides 2 ways:
Way	Use
âœ… abstract class	Partial abstraction (some methods implemented)
âœ… interface	Full abstraction (all methods abstract by default)
ğŸ§ª Example 1: Using abstract class
java
Copy
Edit
abstract class Animal {
    abstract void sound(); // abstract method

    void sleep() {
        System.out.println("Animal sleeps");
    }
}

class Dog extends Animal {
    void sound() {
        System.out.println("Dog barks");
    }
}
java
Copy
Edit
public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Animal a = new Dog();
        a.sound();  // Dog barks
        a.sleep();  // Animal sleeps
    }
}
âœ… Output:
nginx
Copy
Edit
Dog barks  
Animal sleeps
ğŸ§ª Example 2: Using interface
java
Copy
Edit
interface Vehicle {
    void start();     // public + abstract by default
    void stop();
}

class Car implements Vehicle {
    public void start() {
        System.out.println("Car started");
    }

    public void stop() {
        System.out.println("Car stopped");
    }
}
java
Copy
Edit
Vehicle v = new Car();
v.start();
v.stop();
ğŸ” Why Use Abstraction?
Benefit	Description
Data hiding	User ko sirf important cheezein dikhai jati hain
Code clarity	Clean interface, reusable design
Security	Internal logic protected from misuse
Loose coupling	Code change ka impact kam hota hai
ğŸ§  Summary Table:
Concept	Abstract Class	Interface
Partial abstraction	âœ…	âŒ (100% abstraction by default)
Can have constructor	âœ…	âŒ
Multiple inheritance	âŒ (single)	âœ… (via interface)
Method type	abstract + concrete	only abstract (Java 8+ allows default too)